{"TopicId":219017,"ForumId":139,"TopicTitle":"KSP2 Release Notes - Update v0.1.4.0","CreatedByName":"Intercept Games","CreatedById":210281,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T16:55:00Z","PageNum":2,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"KerbolExplorer","CreatedById":177191,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T18:28:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s a very small changelog, is this really the patch we\u0027ve been waiting for the whole summer?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T18:32:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317433\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693420085\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022177191\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KerbolExplorer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, KerbolExplorer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s a very small changelog, is this really the patch we\u0027ve been waiting for the whole summer?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u2019s some possibilities. Maybe these were bugs that really impacted gameplay and were hard to fix. Instead of low-hanging fruit they went after What Matters. Time will tell if that\u2019s the case.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RocketRockington","CreatedById":223189,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T18:37:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317434\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693420328\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278303\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Kerbart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u2019s some possibilities. Maybe these were bugs that really impacted gameplay and were hard to fix. Instead of low-hanging fruit they went after What Matters. Time will tell if that\u2019s the case.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso possible that developers have been moved on to non-bug fixing tasks, or even other projects.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stoup","CreatedById":2804,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T18:45:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGlad to see some fixes!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan\u0027t deny my own feelings though, quite honestly, the orbital decay bug is what\u0027s kept me from wanting to try to engage with the game, and since it\u0027s not fixed, it\u0027s just back to biding my time with other projects for me!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nestor","CreatedById":163018,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T18:52:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317436\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693420642\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022223189\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RocketRockington\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, RocketRockington said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso possible that developers have been moved on to non-bug fixing tasks, or even other projects.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot other projects but other features. We are always looking for a balance between doing fixes for the next minor update vs future features such as heat, science and others. We are constantly looking at the top reported bugs and we try to fix as many of those as time and other priorities allow.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gluckez","CreatedById":226569,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T19:08:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwell... for those saying this game is \u0022totally unplayable\u0022. I just landed a mun base under the mun arch without quicksaves or bugs. it was just kinda weird to see the fairing drop straight down after deploying but, oh well. ..\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd to the devs: props, great work! it was smooth sailing all the way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: I also noticed these weird round payload structures, are those new? looks really useful to strut things to, but I wish I could attach them to decouplers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-08-30T19:10:03Z\u0022 title=\u002208/30/2023 07:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Aug 30\u0022\u003EAugust 30, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by gluckez\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Ejust extra\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nestor","CreatedById":163018,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T19:14:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317451\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693422519\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022226569\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gluckez\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, gluckez said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit was just kinda weird to see the fairing drop straight down after deploying but, oh well. ..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is one of the ones next in the list to get fixed.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gluckez","CreatedById":226569,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T19:17:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317455\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693422870\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163018\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nestor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, nestor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is one of the ones next in the list to get fixed.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthat\u0027s great, but honestly, if it\u0027s just something cosmetic like that I don\u0027t mind at all. I think heating, wobbliness and science should be prioritized, but I guess that\u0027s not up to me xD. The game is perfectly playable as it is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cocoscacao","CreatedById":225696,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T19:24:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317455\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693422870\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163018\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nestor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, nestor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is one of the ones next in the list to get fixed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile on the subject of fairings... is there any hope that the old system for making them via mouse move is gonna return? I really hate this new mechanic of dragging arrows.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alexoff","CreatedById":145774,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T19:32:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317441\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693421563\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163018\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nestor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, nestor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot other projects but other features. We are always looking for a balance between doing fixes for the next minor update vs future features such as heat, science and others.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll of us on the forum would really like to see these new features in action, and not just rare screenshots\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AtomicTech","CreatedById":210823,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T19:33:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317380\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693416618\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022112420\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ShadowZone\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, ShadowZone said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs your resident patch historian, allow me to present the statistics for this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ctable border=\u00221\u0022 cellpadding=\u00221\u0022 cellspacing=\u00221\u0022 style=\u0022width:500px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ctbody\u003E\n\u003Ctr\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ETotal items\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ECommunity\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E% of total\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\n\u003Ctr\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n0.1.1\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n281\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n42\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n15%\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\n\u003Ctr\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n0.1.2\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n173\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n36\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n21%\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\n\u003Ctr\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n0.1.3\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n165\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n17\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n10%\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\n\u003Ctr\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n0.1.4\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n81\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n9\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n11%\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\n\u003C/tbody\u003E\n\u003C/table\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPatch 4 has less than half the number of fixes than the previous one did. Does this make it worse? Hard to say, since I would assume work on the orbital decay bug must have taken quite a lot of time and developer resources. Which is why the sheer number of fixes rarely gives the full picture of how much of an improvement a patch really is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat being said, I have seen quite a few fixes for construction that will make my life a lot easier! Now to downloading it...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFingers crossed things\u0027ll continue to get better \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gluckez","CreatedById":226569,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T19:39:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit makes sense that less and less bugs are getting fixed. you\u0027re not gonna add extra bugs to fix, and the ones that were done from the start were most likely the easiest ones to fix, so you could do more of them faster.\u003Cbr\u003E\nnow it\u0027s probably harder bugs that aren\u0027t as easy to reproduce and fix. there\u0027s probably a lot of work that has been done towards optimizing the game as well, things that are important for the quality of the codebase\u003Cbr\u003E\nand future features.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Moritz Space","CreatedById":221627,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T19:49:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317380\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693416618\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022112420\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ShadowZone\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, ShadowZone said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs your resident patch historian, allow me to present the statistics for this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ctable border=\u00221\u0022 cellpadding=\u00221\u0022 cellspacing=\u00221\u0022 style=\u0022width:500px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ctbody\u003E\n\u003Ctr\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ETotal items\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ECommunity\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E% of total\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\n\u003Ctr\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n0.1.1\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n281\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n42\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n15%\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\n\u003Ctr\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n0.1.2\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n173\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n36\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n21%\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\n\u003Ctr\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n0.1.3\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n165\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n17\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n10%\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\n\u003Ctr\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n0.1.4\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n81\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n9\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n11%\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\n\u003C/tbody\u003E\n\u003C/table\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPatch 4 has less than half the number of fixes than the previous one did. Does this make it worse? Hard to say, since I would assume work on the orbital decay bug must have taken quite a lot of time and developer resources. Which is why the sheer number of fixes rarely gives the full picture of how much of an improvement a patch really is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat being said, I have seen quite a few fixes for construction that will make my life a lot easier! Now to downloading it...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat are 700 fixes in total which is\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n117 fixes per month\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3.7 fixes per day\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that\u0027s quite good when you keep in mind that they\u0027re working on roadmap features in parallel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nestor","CreatedById":163018,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T19:56:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317462\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693423457\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225696\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cocoscacao\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, cocoscacao said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile on the subject of fairings... is there any hope that the old system for making them via mouse move is gonna return? I really hate this new mechanic of dragging arrows.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou would have to convince \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/83952-nertea/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283952\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/83952-nertea/\u0022 id=\u0022ips_uid_5492_16\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nertea\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0about it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"InterstellarDrifter","CreatedById":223181,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T19:57:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#2e3035;color:#ffffff;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022LIXfqOx.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/LIXfqOx.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#2e3035;color:#ffffff;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u00225v4eYz1.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/5v4eYz1.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#2e3035;color:#ffffff;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003EWhen can we fix this??\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AtomicTech","CreatedById":210823,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T19:59:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317481\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693425395\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163018\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nestor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, nestor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou would have to convince \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/83952-nertea/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283952\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/83952-nertea/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nertea\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0about it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/83952-nertea/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283952\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/83952-nertea/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nertea\u003C/a\u003E...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022spongebob-squarepants-begging.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002295.78\u0022 height=\u0022477\u0022 width=\u0022498\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.tenor.com/4IckGuTqWeYAAAAC/spongebob-squarepants-begging.gif\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T20:03:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317455\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693422870\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163018\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nestor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n46 minutes ago, nestor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is one of the ones next in the list to get fixed.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn 1.5, they\u2019ll go up \u00A0instead and explode the ship. In 1.6, they\u2019ll just straight explode and in 1.7 they\u2019ll do what they\u2019re supposed to do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T20:04:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317462\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693423457\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225696\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cocoscacao\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, cocoscacao said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile on the subject of fairings... is there any hope that the old system for making them via mouse move is gonna return? I really hate this new mechanic of dragging arrows.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/83952-nertea/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283952\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/83952-nertea/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nertea\u003C/a\u003E I second this. The system of building fairing by dragging arrows is super clunky and slow. But.. don\u0027t redo the old system. Instead, make the fairing auto-size to cover the payload, so the rockets look nice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-08-30T20:27:30Z\u0022 title=\u002208/30/2023 08:27  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Aug 30\u0022\u003EAugust 30, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Vl3d\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"InterstellarDrifter","CreatedById":223181,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T20:11:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317489\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693425868\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/83952-nertea/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283952\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/83952-nertea/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nertea\u003C/a\u003E I second this. The system of building fairing by dragging arrows is super clumsy and slow. But.. don\u0027t redo the old system. Instead, make the fairing auto-size to cover the payload, so the rockets look nice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the KSP1 system worked very well. It is intuitive, quick, and reliable. Why fix what ain\u0027t broken?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T20:12:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317489\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693425868\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/83952-nertea/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283952\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/83952-nertea/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nertea\u003C/a\u003E I second this. The system of building fairing by dragging arrows is super clumsy and slow. But.. don\u0027t redo the old system. Instead, make the fairing auto-size to cover the payload, so the rockets look nice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can see some issues with this solution, for example, fairings sometimes are just used to make beautiful craft (with empty fairings).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, I disagree, I like the new system, it lets you make more accurate movements (In theory), while moving around the ship. It just needs some tweak to make it feels better, like for instance the arrow doesn\u0027t follow the mouse well, it\u0027s slower as if there was a max speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd there is an annoying bug where the \u0022preview\u0022 fairing isn\u0027t exactly what you have at the end when you click to confirm it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut if those get fixed, I\u0027m sure the system is as viable and enjoyable than ksp1 fairings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-08-30T20:13:54Z\u0022 title=\u002208/30/2023 08:13  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Aug 30\u0022\u003EAugust 30, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Spicat\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T20:15:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317496\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693426377\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022228085\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spicat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Spicat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can see some issues with this solution, for example, fairings sometimes are just used to make beautiful craft (with empty fairings).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, I disagree, I like the new system, it lets you make more accurate movements (In theory), while moving around the ship. It just needs some tweak to make it feels better, like for instance the arrow doesn\u0027t follow the mouse well, it\u0027s slower as if there was a max speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd there is an annoying bug where the \u0022preview\u0022 fairing isn\u0027t exactly what you have at the end when you click to confirm it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut if those get fixed, I\u0027m sure the system is as viable and enjoyable than ksp1 fairings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAuto-adjusting fairings should at least be an option.\u003Cbr\u003E\nVote here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9001733676\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/219079-fairing-adjust-system-how-do-you-prefer-to-interact-with-the-procedural-fairings/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:147px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ShadowZone","CreatedById":112420,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T20:18:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease don\u0027t return to KSP1 fairings. It\u0027s never possible to make a precise shape with them and replicating what you did once is nigh impossible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe new UI is a bit clunky, and I agree that it takes longer, but I can build fairings with a lot more confidence when it comes to more special applications that require higher degree of precision.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T20:21:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317504\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693426692\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022112420\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ShadowZone\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, ShadowZone said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease don\u0027t return to KSP1 fairings. It\u0027s never possible to make a precise shape with them and replicating what you did once is nigh impossible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe new UI is a bit clunky, and I agree that it takes longer, but I can build fairings with a lot more confidence when it comes to more special applications that require higher degree of precision.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n100% agree. I also often had issues trying to figure out how big to make the fairings in KSP1 because I was unable to move the camera at the same time to try to get some 3d perspective of what I was doing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Razor235","CreatedById":16436,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T20:21:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224315773\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693414500\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210281\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Intercept Games\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Intercept Games said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:1437623226_rocket_1f680(3):\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/1437623226_rocket_1f680(3).png\u0022 title=\u0022:1437623226_rocket_1f680(3):\u0022\u003E\u00A0Improved orbits decaying when vessels are not applying any thrust\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSooo.... what exactly does \u0022improved\u0022 mean in this context?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it actually fixed?\u00A0 Is it just slower or only when not warping?\u00A0 Or is there just one less step in the goat-sacrifice-saltcircle-seance-chanting procedure to ensure that it only happens some of the time maybe?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stephensan","CreatedById":222320,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T20:25:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317508\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219017\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693426896\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002216436\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Razor235\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Razor235 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSooo.... what exactly does \u0022improved\u0022 mean in this context?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it actually fixed?\u00A0 Is it just slower or only when not warping?\u00A0 Or is there just one less step in the goat-sacrifice-saltcircle-seance-chanting procedure to ensure that it only happens some of the time maybe?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfrom rumors of discord, its worse overall and there is more decaying-related issues.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}